{"type":"message","id":"96df7a25","parentId":"8fc7c9ed","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:19:23.520Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2kosh0idpqle_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WebWizard Identity\n\n## Expertise\n- UI/UX Design & Implementation\n- Next.js 14 (App Router)\n- Tailwind CSS (Estilos dinámicos)\n- Framer Motion & GSAP (Animaciones)\n- Supabase Integration (Frontend)\n\n## Resources\n- **Rutas Propias**: `/pruebalo/`, `/embed/`, `/sitio/`, `/dashboard/`.\n- **MCPs**: Supabase, n8n.\n\n## Quality Checklist\n- [ ] Mobile-first responsive\n- [ ] Dark/Light mode support\n- [ ] No hardcoded colors/prices\n- [ ] Optional chaining (?.) in all data access\n- [ ] Loading/Error states handled\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776021563510}}
{"type":"message","id":"49a073b1","parentId":"96df7a25","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:19:37.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. WebWizard, DevGuardian, etc. are defined as identities in folders but they are NOT actually spawned as agents in OpenClaw/OpenCode. They're just documentation/configuration folders. Only Sammy is actually running as an agent.\n\nThe reason WebWizard is \"not available\" is because:\n1. There's only ONE actual agent running: Sammy\n2. The other \"agents\" (WebWizard, DevGuardian, etc.) are just folder configurations/identities\n3. They would need to be spawned as separate sessions/agents to be truly \"available\"\n\nI should explain this clearly to Sam.\n","thinkingSignature":"d5d0a13dfc732b5b09c879fdd4b5c30bceba32db37635ca69886a8da9d498526"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**Explicación clara, Sam:**\n\nHay una diferencia entre:\n\n| Concepto | Descripción | Status |\n|----------|-------------|--------|\n| 🧙 **Carpetas/Identidades** | Archivos de configuración (IDENTITY.md, SOUL.md) | ✅ Existen (WebWizard, DevGuardian, etc.) |\n| 🤖 **Agentes Activos** | Procesos de IA realmente corriendo | ❌ Solo yo (Sammy) |\n\n**WebWizard = Carpeta con docs ✅**  \n**WebWizard = Agente activo ❌**\n\nLos otros 6 roles (DevGuardian, DataAlchemist, GrowthPilot, etc.) están definidos en carpetas pero **NO están instanciados como agentes independientes**.\n\n---\n\n**Para tener agentes realmente independientes, necesitaríamos:**\n\n1. **Spawnear sesiones separadas** para cada rol\n2. **Configurar OpenClaw/OpenCode** para múltiples agentes\n3. **Establecer comunicación** entre ellos\n\n¿Quieres que configure los agentes adicionales como procesos activos, o prefieres seguir con el modelo actual donde yo (Sammy) ejecuto todas las tareas directamente?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":468,"output":354,"cacheRead":47808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48630,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776021563521,"responseId":"062b233b9f071f7821014a709114d542"}}
