{"type":"message","id":"66c97074","parentId":"4f87c372","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:23:01.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I created the message in the shared inbox. Now I should explain to Sam what I did and how this works.\n\nActually, thinking about it more - these agents aren't truly \"active\" in the sense that they'll automatically read this file. They're just configurations waiting to be spawned. \n\nThe real way to do this would be to actually spawn each agent session and have them respond. But that's quite complex and might not be what Sam wants.\n\nLet me explain what I did and give Sam options on how to proceed.\n","thinkingSignature":"e52ba3937cbc95b291cac470324f380f44c5a642ab67493f14e321799eb55e00"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n✅ **Mensaje enviado al inbox compartido.**\n\nLo que hice fue crear un archivo en `/.shared-inbox/NOMBRE_AGENTES.md` con la instrucción para que cada agente se autoconfigure.\n\n---\n\n⚠️ **Importante, Sam:**\n\nLos agentes **no leen automáticamente** el inbox. Para que respondan真正mente, necesitas:\n\n**Opción A — Spawnear cada agente:**\n```\nSesión → Agente → Prompt con instrucción\n```\n\n**Opción B — Yo losspawn directamente ahora:**\nPuedo usar `sessions_spawn` para invocar cada uno y pedirles que se identifiquen.\n\n---\n\n### 🔥¿Quieres que losspawn ahora y les pida que se autodefinan?\n\nEsto tomaría unos minutos pero sería más interactivo — cada agente te respondería directamente con su nombre, emoji y frase de identidad.\n\n¿Qué prefieres?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":358,"output":280,"cacheRead":55360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55998,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776021770188,"responseId":"062b240af2c2e3ce2cd3202d3a8a3ff6"}}
