{"type":"message","id":"a8ac219f","parentId":"8a90815c","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:36:14.640Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue - the OpenClaw gateway is only listening on localhost (127.0.0.1) on port 4002. This means it's not accessible from external networks even with Tailscale. The gateway needs to either:\n1. Be configured to listen on all interfaces (0.0.0.0), or\n2. Be accessible through Tailscale's own connection handling\n\nSam needs to connect via Tailscale. Let me check if there's a Tailscale ACL or if we can connect via the Tailscale IP (100.85.125.102).\n\nActually, looking at the openclaw.json config, the gateway is configured with:\n```json\n\"gateway\": {\n  \"mode\": \"local\",\n  \"port\": 4002,\n  \"auth\": {\n    \"mode\": \"token\",\n    \"token\": \"fca2235a378d3882993e733b5b15b729\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe mode is \"local\" which means it only listens on localhost. To make it accessible via Tailscale, we'd need to change it or use a proxy.\n\nLet me test if the gateway is accessible via the Tailscale IP from this same machine.\n","thinkingSignature":"de2b342b508263413376fb5744c1a58fba0142b0cdeac2b98fa476ebb693e2f7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jgsj7ux2z85n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --connect-timeout 5 http://100.85.125.102:4002/health 2>/dev/null || echo \"Gateway not reachable via Tailscale IP on port 4002\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jgsj7ux2z85n_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | grep -A5 '\"gateway\"'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":326,"output":352,"cacheRead":78912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79590,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776022564728,"responseId":"062b2725bff2d242ce1e4d1493b547b9"}}
