{"type":"message","id":"7af92336","parentId":"3a849b96","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:38:09.222Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam wants both:\n1. Local access (keep it working)\n2. Remote access via Tailscale\n\nAnd he wants to know if after the restart he needs to do anything to activate me or if it happens automatically.\n\nI need to:\n1. Modify the gateway config to listen on Tailscale IP (or 0.0.0.0)\n2. Configure it properly\n3. Explain that after restart it auto-starts (systemd service or similar)\n4. Then execute the change\n\nLet me first check the current gateway config and then patch it to listen on all interfaces.\n","thinkingSignature":"3eafd7529d6bfc4947c40e5a2d68b3fc56f6d5d343f72356d4589145a710cb4b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rkynbqikubqs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user status openclaw 2>/dev/null || systemctl status openclaw 2>/dev/null || ps aux | grep openclaw | grep -v grep"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rkynbqikubqs_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /home/travis/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log 2>/dev/null || ls ~/.openclaw/logs/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":287,"output":231,"cacheRead":79680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776022681753,"responseId":"062b279a650a927fada44c19303110c0"}}
