{"type":"message","id":"8ca91477","parentId":"eb7b033b","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:38:29.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the proper schema for the gateway config. The mode can only be \"local\" or \"remote\", not \"both\". Let me look at what remote mode does and if it binds to all interfaces.\n","thinkingSignature":"16fe03f64d44f8c747b0e54ed34ca56dabdf4c21f8c1e970929b59cf518f1914"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u3b062g4f9d1_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"gateway"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":186,"output":80,"cacheRead":80704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776022707027,"responseId":"062b27b331c2a08bf4c5a2f36c095f17"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b02e54c","parentId":"8ca91477","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:38:30.477Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u3b062g4f9d1_1","toolName":"gateway","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"path\": \"gateway\",\n    \"schema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"title\": \"Gateway\",\n      \"description\": \"Gateway runtime surface for bind mode, auth, control UI, remote transport, and operational safety controls. Keep conservative defaults unless you intentionally expose the gateway beyond trusted local interfaces.\"\n    },\n    \"hint\": {\n      \"label\": \"Gateway\",\n      \"group\": \"Gateway\",\n      \"order\": 30,\n      \"help\": \"Gateway runtime surface for bind mode, auth, control UI, remote transport, and operational safety controls. Keep conservative defaults unless you intentionally expose the gateway beyond trusted local interfaces.\",\n      \"tags\": [\n        \"advanced\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"hintPath\": \"gateway\",\n    \"children\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"port\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.port\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Port\",\n          \"help\": \"TCP port used by the gateway listener for API, control UI, and channel-facing ingress paths. Use a dedicated port and avoid collisions with reverse proxies or local developer services.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.port\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"mode\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.mode\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Mode\",\n          \"help\": \"Gateway operation mode: \\\"local\\\" runs channels and agent runtime on this host, while \\\"remote\\\" connects through remote transport. Keep \\\"local\\\" unless you intentionally run a split remote gateway topology.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.mode\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"bind\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.bind\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Bind Mode\",\n          \"help\": \"Network bind profile: \\\"auto\\\", \\\"lan\\\", \\\"loopback\\\", \\\"custom\\\", or \\\"tailnet\\\" to control interface exposure. Keep \\\"loopback\\\" or \\\"auto\\\" for safest local operation unless external clients must connect.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.bind\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"customBindHost\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.customBindHost\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Custom Bind Host\",\n          \"help\": \"Explicit bind host/IP used when gateway.bind is set to custom for manual interface targeting. Use a precise address and avoid wildcard binds unless external exposure is required.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.customBindHost\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"controlUi\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.controlUi\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Control UI\",\n          \"help\": \"Control UI hosting settings including enablement, pathing, and browser-origin/auth hardening behavior. Keep UI exposure minimal and pair with strong auth controls before internet-facing deployments.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.controlUi\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"auth\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.auth\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Auth\",\n          \"help\": \"Authentication policy for gateway HTTP/WebSocket access including mode, credentials, trusted-proxy behavior, and rate limiting. Keep auth enabled for every non-loopback deployment.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.auth\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"trustedProxies\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.trustedProxies\",\n        \"type\": \"array\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Trusted Proxy CIDRs\",\n          \"help\": \"CIDR/IP allowlist of upstream proxies permitted to provide forwarded client identity headers. Keep this list narrow so untrusted hops cannot impersonate users.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.trustedProxies\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"allowRealIpFallback\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.allowRealIpFallback\",\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Allow x-real-ip Fallback\",\n          \"help\": \"Enables x-real-ip fallback when x-forwarded-for is missing in proxy scenarios. Keep disabled unless your ingress stack requires this compatibility behavior.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"access\",\n            \"network\",\n            \"reliability\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.allowRealIpFallback\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"tools\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.tools\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Tool Exposure Policy\",\n          \"help\": \"Gateway-level tool exposure allow/deny policy that can restrict runtime tool availability independent of agent/tool profiles. Use this for coarse emergency controls and production hardening.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.tools\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"webchat\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.webchat\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"channelHealthCheckMinutes\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.channelHealthCheckMinutes\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Channel Health Check Interval (min)\",\n          \"help\": \"Interval in minutes for automatic channel health probing and status updates. Use lower intervals for faster detection, or higher intervals to reduce periodic probe noise.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\",\n            \"reliability\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.channelHealthCheckMinutes\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Channel Stale Event Threshold (min)\",\n          \"help\": \"How many minutes a connected channel can go without receiving any event before the health monitor treats it as a stale socket and triggers a restart. Default: 30.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"channelMaxRestartsPerHour\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.channelMaxRestartsPerHour\",\n        \"type\": \"integer\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": false,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Channel Max Restarts Per Hour\",\n          \"help\": \"Maximum number of health-monitor-initiated channel restarts allowed within a rolling one-hour window. Once hit, further restarts are skipped until the window expires. Default: 10.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\",\n            \"performance\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.channelMaxRestartsPerHour\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"tailscale\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.tailscale\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Tailscale\",\n          \"help\": \"Tailscale integration settings for Serve/Funnel exposure and lifecycle handling on gateway start/exit. Keep off unless your deployment intentionally relies on Tailscale ingress.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.tailscale\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"remote\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.remote\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Remote Gateway\",\n          \"help\": \"Remote gateway connection settings for direct or SSH transport when this instance proxies to another runtime host. Use remote mode only when split-host operation is intentionally configured.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.remote\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"reload\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.reload\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Config Reload\",\n          \"help\": \"Live config-reload policy for how edits are applied and when full restarts are triggered. Keep hybrid behavior for safest operational updates unless debugging reload internals.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\",\n            \"reliability\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.reload\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"tls\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.tls\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway TLS\",\n          \"help\": \"TLS certificate and key settings for terminating HTTPS directly in the gateway process. Use explicit certificates in production and avoid plaintext exposure on untrusted networks.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.tls\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"http\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.http\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway HTTP API\",\n          \"help\": \"Gateway HTTP API configuration grouping endpoint toggles and transport-facing API exposure controls. Keep only required endpoints enabled to reduce attack surface.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.http\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"push\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.push\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Gateway Push Delivery\",\n          \"help\": \"Push-delivery settings used by the gateway when it needs to wake or notify paired devices. Configure relay-backed APNs here for official iOS builds; direct APNs auth remains env-based for local/manual builds.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"network\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"gateway.push\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"nodes\",\n        \"path\": \"gateway.nodes\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"result":{"path":"gateway","schema":{"type":"object","additionalProperties":false,"title":"Gateway","description":"Gateway runtime surface for bind mode, auth, control UI, remote transport, and operational safety controls. Keep conservative defaults unless you intentionally expose the gateway beyond trusted local interfaces."},"hint":{"label":"Gateway","group":"Gateway","order":30,"help":"Gateway runtime surface for bind mode, auth, control UI, remote transport, and operational safety controls. Keep conservative defaults unless you intentionally expose the gateway beyond trusted local interfaces.","tags":["advanced"]},"hintPath":"gateway","children":[{"key":"port","path":"gateway.port","type":"integer","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Port","help":"TCP port used by the gateway listener for API, control UI, and channel-facing ingress paths. Use a dedicated port and avoid collisions with reverse proxies or local developer services.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.port"},{"key":"mode","path":"gateway.mode","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Mode","help":"Gateway operation mode: \"local\" runs channels and agent runtime on this host, while \"remote\" connects through remote transport. Keep \"local\" unless you intentionally run a split remote gateway topology.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.mode"},{"key":"bind","path":"gateway.bind","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Bind Mode","help":"Network bind profile: \"auto\", \"lan\", \"loopback\", \"custom\", or \"tailnet\" to control interface exposure. Keep \"loopback\" or \"auto\" for safest local operation unless external clients must connect.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.bind"},{"key":"customBindHost","path":"gateway.customBindHost","type":"string","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Custom Bind Host","help":"Explicit bind host/IP used when gateway.bind is set to custom for manual interface targeting. Use a precise address and avoid wildcard binds unless external exposure is required.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.customBindHost"},{"key":"controlUi","path":"gateway.controlUi","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Control UI","help":"Control UI hosting settings including enablement, pathing, and browser-origin/auth hardening behavior. Keep UI exposure minimal and pair with strong auth controls before internet-facing deployments.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.controlUi"},{"key":"auth","path":"gateway.auth","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Auth","help":"Authentication policy for gateway HTTP/WebSocket access including mode, credentials, trusted-proxy behavior, and rate limiting. Keep auth enabled for every non-loopback deployment.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.auth"},{"key":"trustedProxies","path":"gateway.trustedProxies","type":"array","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Trusted Proxy CIDRs","help":"CIDR/IP allowlist of upstream proxies permitted to provide forwarded client identity headers. Keep this list narrow so untrusted hops cannot impersonate users.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.trustedProxies"},{"key":"allowRealIpFallback","path":"gateway.allowRealIpFallback","type":"boolean","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Allow x-real-ip Fallback","help":"Enables x-real-ip fallback when x-forwarded-for is missing in proxy scenarios. Keep disabled unless your ingress stack requires this compatibility behavior.","tags":["access","network","reliability"]},"hintPath":"gateway.allowRealIpFallback"},{"key":"tools","path":"gateway.tools","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Tool Exposure Policy","help":"Gateway-level tool exposure allow/deny policy that can restrict runtime tool availability independent of agent/tool profiles. Use this for coarse emergency controls and production hardening.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.tools"},{"key":"webchat","path":"gateway.webchat","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true},{"key":"channelHealthCheckMinutes","path":"gateway.channelHealthCheckMinutes","type":"integer","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Channel Health Check Interval (min)","help":"Interval in minutes for automatic channel health probing and status updates. Use lower intervals for faster detection, or higher intervals to reduce periodic probe noise.","tags":["network","reliability"]},"hintPath":"gateway.channelHealthCheckMinutes"},{"key":"channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes","path":"gateway.channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes","type":"integer","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Channel Stale Event Threshold (min)","help":"How many minutes a connected channel can go without receiving any event before the health monitor treats it as a stale socket and triggers a restart. Default: 30.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.channelStaleEventThresholdMinutes"},{"key":"channelMaxRestartsPerHour","path":"gateway.channelMaxRestartsPerHour","type":"integer","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Channel Max Restarts Per Hour","help":"Maximum number of health-monitor-initiated channel restarts allowed within a rolling one-hour window. Once hit, further restarts are skipped until the window expires. Default: 10.","tags":["network","performance"]},"hintPath":"gateway.channelMaxRestartsPerHour"},{"key":"tailscale","path":"gateway.tailscale","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Tailscale","help":"Tailscale integration settings for Serve/Funnel exposure and lifecycle handling on gateway start/exit. Keep off unless your deployment intentionally relies on Tailscale ingress.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.tailscale"},{"key":"remote","path":"gateway.remote","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Remote Gateway","help":"Remote gateway connection settings for direct or SSH transport when this instance proxies to another runtime host. Use remote mode only when split-host operation is intentionally configured.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.remote"},{"key":"reload","path":"gateway.reload","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Config Reload","help":"Live config-reload policy for how edits are applied and when full restarts are triggered. Keep hybrid behavior for safest operational updates unless debugging reload internals.","tags":["network","reliability"]},"hintPath":"gateway.reload"},{"key":"tls","path":"gateway.tls","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway TLS","help":"TLS certificate and key settings for terminating HTTPS directly in the gateway process. Use explicit certificates in production and avoid plaintext exposure on untrusted networks.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.tls"},{"key":"http","path":"gateway.http","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway HTTP API","help":"Gateway HTTP API configuration grouping endpoint toggles and transport-facing API exposure controls. Keep only required endpoints enabled to reduce attack surface.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.http"},{"key":"push","path":"gateway.push","type":"object","required":false,"hasChildren":true,"hint":{"label":"Gateway Push Delivery","help":"Push-delivery settings used by the gateway when it needs to wake or notify paired devices. Configure relay-backed APNs here for official iOS builds; direct APNs auth remains env-based for local/manual builds.","tags":["network"]},"hintPath":"gateway.push"},