{"type":"message","id":"d652cda6","parentId":"5085704d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:45:57.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now. The gateway is still binding only to `127.0.0.1:4002` and `[::1]:4002` (localhost only). The `bind: tailnet` change didn't actually make it listen on the Tailscale IP.\n\nLooking at the listening ports:\n```\nLISTEN 0      511                      127.0.0.1:4002       0.0.0.0:*    \nLISTEN 0      511                          [::1]:4002          [::]:*    \n```\n\nThe gateway is NOT listening on `100.85.125.102:4002`. The `tailnet` bind mode might not work as expected or requires Tailscale Serve functionality.\n\nLet me check the gateway config more carefully and see what's happening. The `tailnet` bind mode might require `tailscale serve` to be set up, not just binding to the IP directly.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I need to use `bind: custom` with `customBindHost: 100.85.125.102`.\n","thinkingSignature":"b625626dd46e1654f9b70e6d9a362110bd6a2f953e67e4c4fedb258ea7886fcc"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n🚨 **PROBLEMA ENCONTRADO:**\n\nEl gateway sigue bindeado solo a **localhost**:\n```\n127.0.0.1:4002  ← Solo local\n[::1]:4002      ← Solo IPv6 local\n```\n\nEl `bind: tailnet` no cambió la interfaz de escucha. Necesito forzarlo manualmente.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2szckyj07p78_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","note":"Forzando bind a IP Tailscale 100.85.125.102 para acceso remoto.","raw":"{\"gateway\":{\"bind\":\"custom\",\"customBindHost\":\"100.85.125.102\"}}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":575,"output":381,"cacheRead":82368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83324,"cost":{"input":0.0001725,"output":0.0004572,"cacheRead":0.00494208,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00557178}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776023146840,"responseId":"062b296b85f9122fc2450bd0d3abb7ae"}}
