{"type":"message","id":"965c9405","parentId":"68219dec","timestamp":"2026-04-12T20:43:52.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway IS running and responding on localhost. The problem is just that it's still bound to localhost only, not to the Tailscale IP. The `bind: \"tailnet\"` setting didn't work as expected - the gateway is still only listening on 127.0.0.1.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe using Tailscale's serve command to expose the local port, or check if there's a way to make the gateway listen on all interfaces.\n","thinkingSignature":"ac054922e0cf5af10d4a101f8bd51d48a57b95f496cecf2d7068bd311a6076e9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n✅ **El gateway está activo** y respondiendo bien en localhost.\n\nEl problema es que sigue bindeado solo a localhost (`127.0.0.1:4002`) — no a la IP de Tailscale (`100.85.125.102`).\n\nVoy a configurar **Tailscale Serve** para exponer el gateway remotamente:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xttgf4mt1pvq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sudo tailscale serve --bg https+insecure://localhost:4002 2>&1 || tailscale serve --bg https+insecure://localhost:4002 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":339,"output":229,"cacheRead":86912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87480,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776026624669,"responseId":"062b370123a885714de27a92c3b5fb93"}}
