{"type":"message","id":"4fd2ac25","parentId":"eb8c461f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T20:50:09.773Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Rebecca tiene una sesión activa (4828e01e-7e4d-4afd-a18a-0eb45ff4d694.jsonl - 1.4MB!) que está siendo escrita ahora (15:49). Tiene un lock file que indica que está en uso. La sesión está activa y procesando.Pero el problema es que Rebecca está \"solo escribiendo\" - esto típicamente significa que está generando una respuesta muy larga o está en un loop infinito.\n\nLet me check the latest messages in that session to see what's happening.\n","thinkingSignature":"a8cb01612262cf137c3fec858ed2ea78c3db62611fc153241678ad3bae34c773"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u4b8h6fv0hzu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -200 ~/.openclaw/agents/rebecca/sessions/4828e01e-7e4d-4afd-a18a-0eb45ff4d694.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nlines = []\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        lines.append(d)\n    except: pass\n\n# Show last 10 messages\nfor msg in lines[-10:]:\n    role = msg.get('role', 'unknown')\n    content = msg.get('content', '')\n    if isinstance(content, list):\n        for c in content:\n            if isinstance(c, dict) and c.get('type') == 'text':\n                content = c.get('text', '')[:300]\n                break\n    print(f'[{role.upper()}]: {str(content)[:300]}')\n    print('---')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":607,"output":332,"cacheRead":71616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72555,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776026999479,"responseId":"062b3877fb037ec900e90b6976afacba"}}
