{"type":"message","id":"417c1e37","parentId":"5e5c41c8","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:08:10.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam says he already has Tailscale installed but doesn't understand how to log in/access. I need to provide simple step-by-step instructions.\n","thinkingSignature":"c60fd316ce84b9281f9eb6cb308fa1ba0f89762157a00f8093e26e75e26d07dd"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n¡Te explico paso a paso! 📋\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 CÓMO CONECTAR A OPENCLAW DESDE TU PC:\n\n### Paso 1: Asegúrate que Tailscale está corriendo\nEn tu PC (Windows/Mac), busca el icono de Tailscale en la bandeja del sistema:\n- 🟢 Verde = conectado\n- 🟡 Amarillo = conectando\n- 🔴 Rojo = desconectado\n\n---\n\n### Paso 2: Conectar a tu tailnet\nAbre una terminal (cmd/powershell en Windows, terminal en Mac) y escribe:\n```bash\ntailscale up\n```\nTe aparecerá un enlace tipo `https://login.tailscale.com/a/...` — ábrelo en tu navegador para autenticar.\n\n---\n\n### Paso 3: Verificar que estás conectado\n```bash\ntailscale status\n```\nDeberías ver tu dispositivo y el servidor `travis-system-product-name`.\n\n---\n\n### Paso 4: Acceder a OpenClaw\nUna vez conectado, abre en tu navegador:\n\n```\nhttps://travis-system-product-name.tailfcaac6.ts.net/?token=fca2235a378d3882993e733b5b15b729\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Si sigue sin funcionar:\n\nDime qué ves cuando ejecutas `tailscale status` en tu PC y te ayudo desde ahí. 🎯"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":489,"output":317,"cacheRead":108480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109286,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776028080868,"responseId":"062b3cb1161a37d7dc9418f101ec0021"}}
