{"type":"message","id":"c116a4ac","parentId":"237408c4","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:10:49.039Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam is getting a DNS error. This means his Tailscale connection might not be on the same tailnet as the server. The DNS `travis-system-product-name.tailfcaac6.ts.net` only resolves within the Tailscale network.\n\nThe issue is that:\n1. The server is on tailnet `tailfcaac6.ts.net`\n2. Sam's Tailscale might be on a different tailnet or not properly connected\n\nLet me check if Sam needs to join the same tailnet. The Tailscale Serve was set up and the domain is `travis-system-product-name.tailfcaac6.ts.net` - Sam needs to be connected to the same Tailscale network to resolve this DNS.\n\nLet me help Sam check if his Tailscale is properly connected.\n","thinkingSignature":"375f4bab89aaf7ab97932cc8b4b6c978feaaa833108c3a2ae976c597f6db0a00"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**DNS_PROBE POSSIBLE** = Tu PC no está conectado a la misma red Tailscale que el servidor.\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 POSIBLE PROBLEMA:\n\nTu Tailscale y el servidor están en **diferentes tailnets** o tu Tailscale **no está conectado**.\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 VERIFICACIÓN EN TU PC:\n\nAbre terminal y ejecuta:\n\n```bash\ntailscale status\n```\n\n**Dime qué te muestra** — debería decir algo como:\n- Tu IP de Tailscale (ej: `100.x.x.x`)\n- El hostname del servidor (`travis-system-product-name`)\n\nSi **NO ves** el servidor en la lista, necesitas:\n\n```bash\ntailscale up\n```\n\nY autenticar en el enlace que te aparezca.\n\n---\n\n## 📡 OTRA OPCIÓN - IP directa:\n\nSi el DNS no funciona, prueba con la **IP directamente**:\n\n```\nhttps://100.85.125.102/?token=fca2235a378d3882993e733b5b15b729\n```\n\n---\n\n**¿Qué te muestra `tailscale status` en tu PC?** 🎯"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":485,"output":395,"cacheRead":109568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110448,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWr