{"type":"message","id":"ebd90f2f","parentId":"c108b8a6","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:44:59.046Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, now I have the VPS info:\n- IP: 31.220.18.39\n- Hostname: wilkiedevs.com\n- SSH port is default 22\n\nFor Álvaro (ArchitectAI), he needs SSH credentials. I can generate a new SSH key and attach it to the VPS, or he needs the existing credentials.\n\nFor Luis (DataAlchemist), he needs confirmation on the DB schema. I'll ask Sam about this.\n\nFor Esteban (GrowthPilot), his workspace exists but the issue might be that when I spawned him, he was running from the home directory instead of the workspace. Let me verify his workspace state file.\n\nLet me:\n1. Create SSH key for Álvaro (ArchitectAI) to access production\n2. Fix the workspace state for GrowthPilot\n3. Ask Sam about the DB schema confirmation for Luis\n4. Create a summary file for each agent with their needs\n\nActually, the SSH credentials for the VPS are managed via Hostinger. I can create public keys via the API and attach them to the VPS. Let me do that.\n","thinkingSignature":"285249bf1ec62721d0713822684d1d2435c03e276399f124f9f8f6c4b3e6304e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c0u2hgsr34lo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 2>/dev/null || echo \"No SSH key exists\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c0u2hgsr34lo_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspaces/growthpilot/workspace-state.json 2>/dev/null || echo \"No state file\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c0u2hgsr34lo_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.ssh/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No .ssh directory\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":782,"output":342,"cacheRead":125184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126308,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776030293135,"responseId":"062b455