{"type":"message","id":"d56b1213","parentId":"e141c91d","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:49:44.857Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam wants me to do a complete analysis of the project including all areas. Let me check the workspace and give a comprehensive overview of where Lookitry stands.\n","thinkingSignature":"c0e35e6e3efce81f3b69f7e6f29f55b8f0d56a3a2b370ec3aaa65a0b87030f9e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3mi3pjeawo60_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/AGENTS.md 2>/dev/null | head -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3mi3pjeawo60_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/backend/src/services/ 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3mi3pjeawo60_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/Lookitry_Brain_Vault/Cerebro/PRD.md 2>/dev/null | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":290,"output":185,"cacheRead":127680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128155,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776030580043,"responseId":"062b46743b8d65c8d1bc910853fa7ab4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6dfbf441","parentId":"d56b1213","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:49:45.297Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3mi3pjeawo60_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":151,"aggregated":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.","cwd":"/home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776030585236}}
