{"type":"message","id":"fabb1a6e","parentId":"be02daaf","timestamp":"2026-04-12T21:53:57.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam wants me to execute the recommendations while being careful not to break anything, and to delegate the tasks to the agents.\n\nI need to use the brainstorming skill properly - I should follow the process. But Sam just said \"hazlo\" - he wants me to execute. Let me think about how to proceed safely.\n\nFollowing the brainstorming skill, I should:\n1. Explore project context (already done)\n2. Ask clarifying questions one at a time\n3. Propose 2-3 approaches\n4. Get approval before implementing\n\nBut Sam said \"hazlo\" - he's giving me permission to proceed. However, the brainstorming skill is a HARD-GATE that requires me to get approval on designs before implementing.\n\nLet me be smart about this. I should:\n1. Start with the safest, highest-impact tasks\n2. Delegate to the appropriate agents\n3. Use verification-before-completion skill after each change\n4. Be very careful about anything that could break the system\n\nGiven the context, I'll start with the safest high-impact items:\n1. Start with security fixes (HSTS, JWT logout) - these are relatively isolated\n2. Then move to UX improvements\n3. Delegate to agents\n\nLet me spawn agents to handle these tasks with proper safety instructions.\n","thinkingSignature":"83c2848eecf5a4a8ea91dd34eb8e58bc1cf974cb8e032e52b9a8fe59b1c8f40f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n¡Entendido, Sam! Ejecución cuidadosa con delegation. 🚀\n\nVoy a crear las tareas con **VERIFICATION-BEFORE-COMPLETION** para cada agente y arrancar por los items más seguros primero.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_box1iv17iduc_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"mode":"run","runtime":"subagent","task":"Eres DevGuardian (Diego) de Lookitry. Sam autorizó ejecutar tareas de seguridad.\n\nTu MISIÓN (con extrema precaución):\n1. Investiga cómo está implementado HSTS actualmente