{"type":"message","id":"0e840caf","parentId":"dbf08c57","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:06:03.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `/api/brands/me` endpoint exists and returns 401 (unauthorized) when not logged in. That's correct behavior - the backend is working fine.The issue is that the frontend dev server at localhost:3000 is serving a built version that might have old routes, OR the `/dashboard` route is correctly server-rendered but the client-side auth check is failing.\n\nLet me check what's really happening. The page loads and shows a spinner forever. This means either:\n1. The Promise.allSettled is hanging\n2. The API calls are failing silently\n3. There's an auth redirect loop\n\nSince the backend returns proper 401 for unauthenticated requests, and the dashboard code uses `Promise.allSettled`, even if one call fails it should still render. The spinner should stop when `mounted` becomes false OR when the state updates.\n\nLet me check if there's a specific issue with the frontend build being stale.","thinkingSignature":"24e64e40edce81d76f09a188940ce0de2439937c78a464bcc2abf461381e457c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxxcz6uu7x04_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/frontend/.next/ 2>/dev/null | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxxcz6uu7x04_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL\\|localhost:3001\" /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/frontend/.env* 2>/dev/null | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxxcz6uu7x04_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/frontend/src/app/dashboard/layout.tsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":270,"output":339,"cacheRead":71616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72225,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776031559485,"responseId":"062b