{"type":"message","id":"175811cf","parentId":"8cfa355f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:06:10.377Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The frontend is configured to use `http://localhost:3001` as the API URL. The backend IS running on port 3001, but the routes at `/api/brands/me` return 401 Unauthorized because there's no auth token provided.\n\nThe dashboard IS loading - it's just that when unauthenticated, it shows the 404 error page. That's the expected behavior for unauthenticated users.\n\nThe real question is: is Sam logged in? Let me check if there's any session/cookie issue. The dashboard uses `brandsService.getCurrentBrand()` which calls `/brands/me`. This requires authentication.\n\nLet me check if the frontend dev server is returning the dashboard page correctly. Earlier we saw it's rendering the \"Cargando...\" spinner, which is the initial state. The question is why it doesn't load.\n\n\nSo the page is displaying a spinner, but then gets stuck or shows a 404 when the API call fails. This is actually normal behavior - the loading state displays first while the authentication check happens, and if there's no valid session, it would redirect to login. Sam might be seeing the spinner indefinitely because the authentication check itself is failing or taking too long. The curl request is showing the 404 error page because there's no session, but Sam would see the loading spinner instead since that's the initial state before any auth check happens. The real issue is probably that the authentication check is stuck or failing silently—either the backend isn't responding to the session validation request, or the session exists but the brands API call is failing. I should verify whether the frontend is even making that initial auth call.\n","thinkingSignature":"1b6c6cfb8a06fdcca1b2ce072dd0f3603cedc8d63940c7b7e932b8b52825a5e0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n96r3qdfznob_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http