    });\n          if (res.ok) {\n\n[123 more lines in file. Use offset=111 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776031577739}}
{"type":"message","id":"a39456be","parentId":"8962ea71","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:06:21.196Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The middleware at line 89-95 is protecting /dashboard routes. It checks for a token cookie and redirects to /login if not present. So the dashboard is showing a loading spinner because:\n\n1. The middleware correctly redirects to /login if there's no token\n2. But /dashboard isn't showing a 302 redirect - instead it's showing the loading spinner\n\nWait, but looking at the HTML response from `/dashboard`, it IS the Next.js HTML with the loading spinner in the body. This suggests either:\n1. Sam IS logged in (has a token) but the API calls are failing\n2. The middleware IS allowing access (because Sam has a token) but the page's `useEffect` is stuck loading\n\n\n3. Sam's cookies are being sent but the backend is rejecting them\n\nLet me test the actual API endpoint with a token to see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"620ea9b81a05a71d75a8e975a9d4f6bb577bce5caa9c7c4272e021fb0070cf10"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wwcpcpqbyy0y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sv \"http://localhost:3001/api/brands/me\" -H \"Cookie: token=dev_test_token\" 2>&1 | grep -E \"< HTTP|{|}\" | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wwcpcpqbyy0y_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"brands/me\\|brands\\.me\" /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/backend/src/routes/brands.routes.ts 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":516,"output":306,"cacheRead":73120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73942,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776031577762,"responseId":"062b4a5ae0478d4dc0369c03ecd5164d"}}
