{"type":"message","id":"aec18719","parentId":"f65db2cc","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:06:38.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the backend is returning \"INVALID_CREDENTIALS\" which is a proper error. So the login API works. The issue is that the frontend can't login because Sam doesn't have a test account set up.\n\nBut wait - Sam is already logged in (he's using the dashboard). So the issue must be that the frontend can't fetch data after being logged in. Let me check if there are any other issues.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the whole problem. Sam says \"porq no me carga el dashboard\". Maybe the issue is:\n1. He's trying to access `/dashboard` but it stays on \"Cargando...\"\n2. The loading spinner never goes away\n\nLooking at the code flow:\n1. Dashboard page starts with `loading = true`\n2. It calls `brandsService.getCurrentBrand()`, `usageService.getUsageStats()`, etc.\n3. If ANY of these fail, it should catch the error and set `loading = false`\n4. Then it renders the actual dashboard\n\nBut wait - looking at line 75: `setLoading(false)` - this is inside a try block. What if an error occurs BEFORE line 75? Like during the Promise.allSettled?\n\nActually no, `Promise.allSettled` never throws - it always resolves. So the loading should be set to false at line 75 regardless of whether the API calls succeed or fail.\n\nHmm, let me look more carefully at the error case. After `Promise.allSettled`:\n- Line 75: `setLoading(false)` is called\n- Lines 76-85: Handle the results\n- Line 129: `if (loading) { <spinner> }`\n\nSo if `setLoading(false)` is called, the spinner should not render.\n\nBut what if there's an error during RENDERING of the dashboard? Like a component throws an error?\n\nOr what if `loading` is never set to `false`? Let me check if there are any async issues...\n\nActually wait - I just realized something. The dashboard is a client component ('use client'). But what if there's a JavaScript error during component initialization?\n\n\nLet me check the browser console for any errors or look at the actual network requests - maybe there's a CORS issue or something with how the requests are being made.\n","thinkingSignature":"77fcb3284e194b849804f99079d58d2cbe0ec4bad502e29ed51dc1f5ca99419b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6wcbouwhu3z6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http://localhost:3001/api/brands/me\" -H \"Cookie: token=fake_token_for_testing\" -v 2>&1 | grep -E \"< HTTP|X-Forwarded|Access-Control\" | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6wcbouwhu3z6_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"Access-Control\\|CORS\\|cors\" /home/travis/Lookitry/Lookitry/backend/src/index.ts 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":261,"output":597,"cacheRead":74432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75290,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776031591916,"responseId":"062b4a6808daf7a5dbc9cab868292b73"}}
