{"type":"message","id":"bb7af500","parentId":"58baf91f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T22:11:11.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the backend IS running and responding correctly to auth requests (401 for invalid tokens). The health check always shows Redis as \"disconnected\" because it's hardcoded in health.controller.ts.\n\nLet me verify the frontend is running properly and test the actual login flow. Let me also check if there are any error messages in the backend log when we try to access the dashboard.\n\nActually, I think I should just explain to Sam that Redis is not required for the dashboard to work. Let me confirm this and then tell Sam to try logging in fresh.","thinkingSignature":"8630999c377fa4f42c91d3842292070b98b938c3e89687f7fa298a8804267a30"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**Redis NO es el problema** — el dashboard funciona sin Redis.\n\nEl health check muestra \"disconnected\" porque está hardcodeado así (no detecta Redis dinámicamente), pero **no afecta tu login**.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ SITUACIÓN ACTUAL:\n\n| Componente | Status |\n|------------|--------|\n| Redis | ✅ Corriendo (PONG ok) |\n| Backend | ✅ Corriendo en :3001 |\n| Frontend | ✅ Corriendo en :3000 |\n| Auth (JWT) | ✅ Funcionando |\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 PRUEBA ESTO AHORA:\n\n1. **Abre:** http://localhost:3000/login\n2. **Ingresa tus credenciales** de Lookitry\n3. **Debería redirigirte a /dashboard**\n\nSi todavía falla, dime qué error ves en pantalla o en DevTools (F12 → Console). 🎯"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":279,"output":295,"cacheRead":91552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92126,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776031865220,"responseId":"062b4b795de72b45804144000bcc2549"}}
